NOTICE: This software is a Python port of the NLvib MATLAB toolbox, originally
developed by Malte Krack and Johann Gross at the University of Stuttgart
(Lehrstuhl fur Strukturdynamik und Schwingungstechnik / Institute for Aircraft
Propulsion Systems, ILA). The original MATLAB code is distributed under the
GNU Lesser General Public License v3 (LGPLv3).

This Python port does not include any MATLAB source code. It is an independent
re-implementation of the algorithms described in:

  Krack, M. & Gross, J. (2019). Harmonic Balance for Nonlinear Vibration
  Problems. Springer. ISBN 978-3-030-14023-6.

Users who require the original MATLAB toolbox should obtain it from:
  https://github.com/maltekrack/NLvib

If you use this software in academic work, please cite both this Python port
and the Krack & Gross (2019) textbook. See CITATION.cff for details.
